<paragraph blockId="32.[164,779,1299,1903]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis box="[164,492,1299,1321]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" box="[297,492,1299,1320]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chotta" status="sp. nov.">Philautus chotta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,598,1300,1321]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from known congeners by the following combination of characters: (1) small adult size (SVL 16.7 ± 
<quantity box="[240,327,1391,1413]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[351,371,1392,1413]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">N</emphasis>
= 7, male; SVL 
<quantity box="[587,687,1391,1413]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" unit="mm" value="20.5">20.5 mm</quantity>
, 
<emphasis box="[711,731,1392,1413]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">N</emphasis>
= 1, female); (2) snout in dorsal view sharply pointed; (3) prominent tubercles on upper eyelid; (4) dark spot on either side towards the vent; (5) vermiculated posterior surface of the shanks; (6) very long hindlimbs, strongly overlapping when folded at right angles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[164,779,1299,1903]" lastBlockId="32.[826,1441,565,1689]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Although this species is morphologically unique, we compare it here with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boulenger, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annandalii">
<emphasis box="[518,778,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Philautus annandalii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger GA" box="[171,367,1636,1658]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" pagination="385" refId="ref43191" refString="Boulenger GA. 1906. Description of two Indian frogs. Journal &amp; Proceedings of Asiatic Society of Bengal, (n. s) 2: 385." type="journal article" year="1906">Boulenger, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[454,664,1636,1658]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tuberohumerus">
<emphasis box="[454,664,1636,1658]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">P. tuberohumerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both of which are of comparable size. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" box="[636,736,1667,1688]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chotta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[636,736,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">P. chotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="32" pageNumber="406" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[360,516,1697,1719]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="32" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annandalii">
<emphasis box="[360,516,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">P. annandalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its sharply pointed snout (vs. oval), canthus rostralis sharp (vs. rounded), upper eyelids with a few prominent tubercles (vs. shagreened), a dark spot on either side towards the vent (vs. absent), inner side of shanks with lightbrown blotches (vs. without markings), tibiotarsal articulation reaches up to nostril when stretched 
<emphasis box="[826,1441,565,587]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Description of the 
<typeStatus box="[1034,1128,565,586]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">holotype</typeStatus>
(all measurements in mm):
</emphasis>
Small frog (SVL 16.0) with a slender body (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1437,596,618]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Figs 24A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[826,909,626,648]" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="32.[164,243,1031,1050]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetId="figure-601@32.[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 25. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4427) photographed on an Indian 5-rupee coin (24-mm in diameter); B, paratype (BNHS 4431) from Ponmudi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445406/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">25A, B</figureCitation>
); head length (HL 5.8) slightly shorter than width (HW 6.0; MN 5.0; MFE 4.0; MBE 1.9); outline of snout in dorsal view sharply pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1430,687,710]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
), snout length (SL 2.6) almost equal to the horizontal diameter of the eye (EL 2.7); canthus rostralis sharp, loreal region acutely concave; distance between posterior margins of eyes (IBE 5.8) 1.7 times the distance between anterior margins of eyes (IFE 3.4); tympanum (TYD 0.8) rather indistinct; supratympanic fold rather indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1133,902,924]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
); tongue without a lingual papilla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[826,1441,565,1689]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Forelimb (FLL 4.0) shorter than hand (HAL 4.6; TFL 2.6); fingers without lateral dermal fringe, webbing absent; subarticular tubercles prominent, rounded, single, III2 and IV2 absent (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1429,1055,1077]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 24C</figureCitation>
); prepollex rather indistinct; palmar tubercle small, rounded; supernumerary tubercles weakly developed on fingers (
<figureCitation box="[959,1059,1146,1169]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 24C</figureCitation>
); nuptial pad present, smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[826,1441,565,1689]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Hindlimbs moderately long, shank (ShL 8.7) longer than thigh (TL 8.3), longer than distance from base of inner metatarsal tubercle to the tip of toe IV (FOL 6.6); distance from heel to tip of toe IV (TFOL 11.1); webbing rather rudimentary (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1280,1299,1321]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 24D</figureCitation>
); reaching up to the third subarticular tubercle on either side of toe IV; dermal fringe along toe V absent; subarticular tubercles rather prominent, rounded, simple, IV2 and V2 weakly developed (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1229,1422,1444]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 24D</figureCitation>
); supernumerary tubercles present throughout.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[826,1441,565,1689]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Skin of snout shagreened, between eyes granular, upper eyelids with a few prominent tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[834,972,1544,1566]" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="32.[164,243,1031,1050]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetId="figure-601@32.[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 25. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4427) photographed on an Indian 5-rupee coin (24-mm in diameter); B, paratype (BNHS 4431) from Ponmudi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445406/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 25A, B</figureCitation>
), side of head shagreened to slightly granular, anterior and posterior parts of back, upper and lower parts of flank shagreened; throat shagreened to glandular, chest slightly granular; belly and thigh prominently granular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[826,1441,1728,1903]" lastBlockId="33.[144,759,198,862]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="407" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis box="[826,1055,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">
Colour of 
<typeStatus box="[954,1049,1728,1749]" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
In life: dorsum yellowish grey (
<figureCitation box="[834,932,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="32.[164,243,1031,1050]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetId="figure-601@32.[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 25. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4427) photographed on an Indian 5-rupee coin (24-mm in diameter); B, paratype (BNHS 4431) from Ponmudi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445406/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="406">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
) with various numbers of light-brown, tan, and brown markings, a pair of dark lines between eyes, filled with light brown, an hourglass-shaped area that is slightly darker than the dorsum, a dark spot towards the hindlimb, forming a continuation of the largest leg bar when limbs are flexed into normal sitting posture, lateral abdominal area light brown, tinged with bronze, tympanic region light brown; iris light-grey–brown with dark-brown cross band, encircled with light golden ring; forelimbs and hindlimbs light brown, with dark-brown cross bands, finger tips grey, anterior and posterior margins of thigh light brown; ventral side off white, with various numbers of brown, light-grey and pale-yellow spots forming a vermiculated pattern, throat darkbrownish yellow, margins with dark bands interrupted with white bands, foot and hand light grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[144,759,198,862]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">
In preservation: dark-grey dorsum with light-brown spots, lateral region light brown, a black spot on either side towards the vent (
<figureCitation box="[562,662,626,648]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="31.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[306,1260,1303,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-466@31.[303,1263,1300,1823]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 24. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. (BNHS 4427). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view of head; C, ventral view of hand; D, ventral view of foot. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445404/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
); darkbrownish band between eye and groin enclosing an hourglass marking filled with grey, loreal and tympanic regions grey with irregular white patches, dorsal surface of forelimb and hindlimb light grey with dark-brown cross bands; ventral side uniformly greyish with irregular spots, tibia with brownish black markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[144,759,902,1260]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis box="[144,256,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Variation:</emphasis>
Measurements of 
<specimenCount box="[506,701,902,924]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
are given in 
<tableCitation box="[253,338,932,954]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="10.[113,177,400,421]" captionText="Table 2. Morphometric measurements (in mm) of the specimens used in this study" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Table 2</tableCitation>
. The dorsal coloration is relatively constant in the 
<typeStatus box="[339,388,963,984]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">type</typeStatus>
series, but 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="BNHS" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" specimenCode="BNHS 4432" specimenCount="1">
<specimenCode box="[538,679,963,984]" collectionCode="BNHS" country="India" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8g20-8f2r" name="Bombay Natural History Society" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">BNHS 4432</specimenCode>
has a uniform dark-grey dorsum with a triangular lightgrey snout from the tip to just above the level of the eyes, a dark-grey stripe between the eyes, and a pair of creamy bands on dorsum
</materialsCitation>
; 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="BNHS" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" specimenCode="BNHS 4428, BNHS 4431" specimenCount="1">
<specimenCode box="[479,617,1085,1106]" collectionCode="BNHS" country="India" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8g20-8f2r" name="Bombay Natural History Society" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">BNHS 4428</specimenCode>
has a darkgrey dorsum with a dark band in between the eyes, and a faintly greyish brown longitudinal marking on the dorsum. In captivity (
<specimenCode box="[445,586,1177,1198]" collectionCode="BNHS" country="India" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8g20-8f2r" name="Bombay Natural History Society" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">BNHS 4431</specimenCode>
, 
<figureCitation box="[600,699,1177,1199]" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="32.[164,243,1031,1050]" captionTargetBox="[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetId="figure-601@32.[168,777,195,1001]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figure 25. Holotype of Philautus chotta sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4427) photographed on an Indian 5-rupee coin (24-mm in diameter); B, paratype (BNHS 4431) from Ponmudi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445406/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Fig. 25B</figureCitation>
), the colour changes from light greyish brown to dark brown
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[144,758,1299,1352]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis box="[144,269,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" box="[525,595,1299,1320]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chotta">
<emphasis box="[525,595,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">chotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hindi word) means small, referring to the diminutive adult size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[144,759,1391,1902]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis box="[144,719,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">
Distribution and natural history: 
<taxonomicName authority="Biju &amp; Bossuyt, 2009" authorityName="Biju &amp; Bossuyt" authorityYear="2009" box="[529,719,1391,1412]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chotta" status="sp. nov.">Philautus chotta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="33" pageNumber="407" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known only from the type locality, Ponmudi (
<figureCitation box="[152,250,1452,1474]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="30.[164,243,1842,1861]" captionTargetBox="[184,1422,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-0@30.[182,1425,194,1813]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figure 23. Distribution map. A, Philautus chlorosomma sp nov.; B, Philautus chotta sp. nov.; C, Philautus chromasynchysi sp. nov.; D, Philautus coonoorensis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445402/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[276,358,1452,1475]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[164,228,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Collection localities that are discussed in the text. Localities are arranged by state" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Table 1</tableCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[460,557,1452,1474]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount box="[641,759,1452,1474]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" type="male">five male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[144,257,1483,1504]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">paratypes</typeStatus>
were collected from leaves of a tea plant (at about 1-m height) from an abandoned tea plantation near disturbed evergreen forest patches. All were located by their calls during a rainy night. The sixth female 
<typeStatus box="[231,335,1606,1627]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">paratype</typeStatus>
, FMNH 218101, was collected from the ground along with other 12 other individuals by Inger and Shaffer ‘either on the surface of dead leaves (
<specimenCount box="[152,291,1697,1719]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" type="generic">9 specimens</specimenCount>
) or beneath leaves or logs (
<specimenCount box="[606,747,1697,1719]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" type="generic">4 specimens</specimenCount>
)’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Inger RF &amp; Shaffer HB &amp; Koshy M &amp; Bakde R" box="[151,362,1728,1750]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" pagination="551 - 570" refId="ref43700" refString="Inger RF, Shaffer HB, Koshy M, Bakde R. 1984. A report on a collection of amphibians and reptiles from the Ponmudi, Kerala, South India. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society 81: 551 - 570." type="journal article" year="1984">
Inger 
<emphasis box="[227,283,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">et al.</emphasis>
, 1984
</bibRefCitation>
). During the present study, this species was surveyed at night-time, and all of the individuals were located at an average height of about 
<quantity box="[144,188,1820,1841]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
, although a few individuals were sighted on the forest floor in the daytime during the non-breeding season.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[806,1421,198,281]" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis box="[806,914,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">Remarks:</emphasis>
The new species was ascribed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rao" authorityYear="1937" box="[1307,1421,198,219]" class="Amphibia" family="Rhacophoridae" genus="Philautus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="charius">
<emphasis box="[1307,1421,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">P. charius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(FMNH 218101, FMNH 218107) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Inger RF &amp; Shaffer HB &amp; Koshy M &amp; Bakde R" pageId="33" pageNumber="407" pagination="551 - 570" refId="ref43700" refString="Inger RF, Shaffer HB, Koshy M, Bakde R. 1984. A report on a collection of amphibians and reptiles from the Ponmudi, Kerala, South India. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society 81: 551 - 570." type="journal article" year="1984">
Inger 
<emphasis box="[1365,1421,228,250]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="407">et al.</emphasis>
(1984)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
